Phrynopus kotosh is a species of frogs in the family Craugastoridae. It is endemic to Peru and only known from its type locality near Huancapallac, Hu√°nuco Region, at 2,950 m (9,680 ft) asl in the Cordillera Central (Peruvian Andes). The specific name refers to the pre-Columbian culture Kotosh; ruins from this culture are known from the area of the type locality.